v1.30.3 - SECURITY: enforce API-token scopes on every route (S-2)

API tokens were minted with a scopes:string[] array (UI prompted for
tasks:read,tasks:write) but the route layer NEVER inspected it. A
tasks:read token could DELETE any task or mint a *-scoped token via
POST /api/settings/api-tokens. Patched.

Fix:
- New lib/scopes.ts is the single source of truth for the vocabulary:
  *, tasks:read|write, comments:read|write, projects:read|write,
  webhooks:manage, admin. Ten strings, intentionally small.
- New middleware/requireScope(scope) Fastify preHandler. JWT sessions
  pass implicitly (no apiTokenScopes on request); API tokens must
  carry * or the exact scope. Composes WITH the existing requireAuth
  / requirePermission / requireTeamRole / requireGlobalAdmin gates.
- New requireSessionAuth (defense in depth) rejects ANY API-token
  request even *-scoped. Wired into POST/DELETE /api/settings/api-tokens
  (closes the token-laundering chain), PATCH /api/auth/me/preferences,
  and POST /api/auth/2fa/{setup,confirm,disable,recovery-codes} (a
  wildcard token must not be able to disable a user's 2FA — pairs with
  the v1.30.1 S-3 fix on the pending-token side).
- schemas/apiTokens.ts restricts create-body scopes to z.enum(SCOPES).
  Existing rows with arbitrary scope strings still load but never
  match a gate (effectively no-op until rotated).

Route coverage: every routes/*.ts audited. Every write + most reads
sit behind requireScope or requireSessionAuth. Intentionally unscoped:
system.ts (public), auth.ts bootstrap routes, notificationsWs (JWT-only
by construction), SCIM (its own bearer-token auth).

8 new S-2 tests in apiTokensAndWebhooks.test.ts:
  tasks:read 403 on POST + 403 on DELETE; 200 on GET
  * token 201 on POST + 204 on DELETE
  JWT session unaffected (201 on POST)
  comments:write only 403 on task DELETE (no implicit read=write)
  invented scope rejected at create time (400)
  * API token cannot mint another API token (403)
  * API token cannot disable 2FA (403)

Verified: tsc clean. Full suite 281 passed, 5 skipped (LDAP).